As Engrossed: S1/30/25 SB58
1 Legislative Council:
2 (1) The number of pharmacy permit applications under § 17-92-405
3 received for each of the following types of permits:
4 (A) A pharmacy permit;
5 (B) A specialty permit;
6 (C) A hospital pharmaceutical services permit;
7 (D) An ambulatory care center pharmacy permit; and
8 (E) A retail pharmacy permit;
9 (2) The number of pharmacy permit applications under § 17-92-405
10 approved by the board for each of the following types of permits:
11 (A) A pharmacy permit;
12 (B) A specialty permit;
13 (C) A hospital pharmaceutical services permit;
14 (D) An ambulatory care center pharmacy permit; and
15 (E) A retail pharmacy permit;
16 (3) The total number of retail pharmacies licensed by the board;
17 and
18 (4) The total number of retail pharmacy closings in the state.
19
20 SECTION 5. Arkansas Code § 17-92-607 is repealed.
21 17-92-607. Unlawful for hospital to hold licensed pharmacy permit —
22 Exceptions.
23 (a) It shall be unlawful for any nonprofit, tax exempt, or
24 governmentally funded hospital to acquire direct or indirect interest in or
25 otherwise hold directly or indirectly a licensed pharmacy permit pursuant to
26 the provisions of § 17-92-405, for the sale at retail of drugs and medicines.
27 (b)(1) However, this section does not prohibit any hospital having a
28 direct or indirect interest in or otherwise holding either directly or
29 indirectly a permit before March 28, 1975, from continuing to have an
30 interest in or holding the permit.
31 (2) This section does not prohibit any hospital so holding a
32 permit before March 28, 1975, from receiving a renewal of the permit.
33 (3) This section does not prohibit dispensing drugs or
34 medications through a hospital pharmacy continuity of care endorsement or to
35 hospital employees and students.
